WEST NILE VIRUS, BIRDS, 2003 - RUSSIA (SIBERIA)
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 26 Apr 2004
From: Valery B Loktev <loktev@vector.nsc.ru>
Confirmed circulation of West Nile virus in Western Siberia in 2003
-------------------------------------------------------------------
In the summer of 2003, West Nile virus (WNV) was found in 2 species of
birds collected in the south of Western Siberia. 32 samples (18 birds were
dead) were collected in the Karasuk region of the Novosibirsk province and
were analyzed by anti-WNV monoclonal antibody-modified immunoenzyme assay
(EIA) for antigen detection and by reverse transcriptase polymerase chain
reaction (RT-PCR).
2 positive samples (EIA and RT-PCR positive) from rooks (_Corvus
frugilegus_) [crow family] and 2 positive samples from grey crow (_Corvus
tristis_) were found to be infected with WNV. Sequencing of fragments of
the E protein gene showed the maximum level of homology with strain
WNV/LEIV-Vlg99-27889, a strain of WNV isolated in Volgograd, Russia, in
1999, and Siberian variants of WNV isolated in 2002 [see: ProMED-mail post:
"West Nile virus, birds, 2002 - Russia (Siberia) 20030516.1216].
The high level of homology between these sequences suggests a connection
between West Nile viruses circulating in the Caspian Sea region and Western
Siberia. These results confirm the results of study of field samples
obtained in 2002, indicating that WNV is actively circulating on the south
part of Western Siberia.
[This report was contributed by VA Ternovoi, MA Shestopalov, EV
Protopopova, Yu V Kononova, and VB Loktev from the State Research Center of
Virology and Biotechnology "Vector", Koltsovo, Novosibirsk Region, Russia,
and AV Druzyaka from the Institute of Animal Systematics and Ecology,
Siberian Branch of Russian Academy of Sciences, Novosibirsk, Russia]
--
Valery B Loktev Professor, DrSci, MD, PhD
Head of Department Molecular Virology
Deputy Director, Institute of Molecular Biology
State Research Center of Virology & Biotechnology "VECTOR"
Koltsovo, Novosibirsk region, 630559
