<loktev@vector.nsc.ru>
[ProMED-mail thanks the VECTOR group for this update. West Nile virus is
endemic in localities along the flight paths of migratory birds from South
Africa across the Mediterranean Sea to Europe and Siberia, but human cases
are not commonly reported in these regions. - Mod.CP/JW]
